Left Rotate Array by One
Input: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
Output: [2, 3, 4, 5, 1]
Move the first element to the end, and shift all other elements one position to the left.

function leftRotateByOne(arr) {
  if (arr.length === 0) return arr;

  let first = arr[0];

  for (let i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
    arr[i - 1] = arr[i];
  }

  arr[arr.length - 1] = first;
  return arr;
}

// Example
console.log(leftRotateByOne([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]));

Time Complexity:  O(n)
Because we shift every element once (loop runs through the whole array).

Space Complexity:  O(1)
No extra array is used ‚Äî rotation is done in-place.(in original array)
